cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.FL, cs.DS

This paper deals with constraint solving in nominal abstract syntax, which involves reasoning about binders. This is a topic that is commonly studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the Urban-Pitts-Gabbay nominal unification algorithm, which is a well-known algorithm in the area of computational logic (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper presents a novel algorithm for solving constraints over a variant of nominal abstract syntax, which involves issues of termination and translation, making it relevant to the areas of formal languages (cs.FL) and data structures (cs.DS).
